"http://wyborcza.pl/1,76842,4865974.html",The 'Power-holding Group' - Case Discontinued but Not Cleared Up,"0
The Białystok prosecutors said yesterday they had ultimately discontinued the inquiry into the 'power-holding group'.","It was the group that, when the post-communist Democratic Left Alliance was in power, sent film producer Lew Rywin to Agora, the publisher of Gazeta Wyborcza, with a corruption offer. That the group really existed was confirmed by the court in the explication of Rywin's sentence, but no names were mentioned. The prosecutors were to determine the group's line-up, but now they have given up.

This is bad news, because it means that the scandal's key perpetrators will not be punished. The prosecutors had failed to break the conspiracy of silence of the people involved in the scandal, so finding conclusive evidence against the 'power-holding group' and drawing up a convincing indictment was very difficult. It is necessary, though it's not easy, to accept the fact that the judiciary is not always able to punish the culprits.",Dominika Wielowieyska (Fot. Sławomir Kamiński / AG),
